originalText: cc_al_fabet
Start Element
alfabet
I just gotta unload some of this stuff and I'm off!

::Before you stands a man dressed as Junkyard. Large rucksack out of which metal pipes, fishing rods and gun barrels stick out; patched pockets full of forks, screwdrivers and used flares; stained rathound skin bags dangling from his belt, pulling on it as if they were full of lead-filled bowling balls. All these things combined must weight twice as much as him, you feel, and it forces you to simply stand in awe at the durability of this man's legs and back.

Then, he speaks through his mask.::

Excuse me, $(#sir/ma'am), but how would you like to buy these wonderful animal organs and leather? Or these chrome-plated quad handles? I, a well-known scavenger that goes by the name Al Fabet, have so many unique and exciting trinkets to sell and only need a buyer.
context.npc_cc_alfabet_sendDeepCaverns
context.npc_cc_alfabet_met
Care to buy my organs? I mean - care to buy animal organs from me?
No one wants to buy my stuff. C'mon people, what's wrong with you all!?
This is so stupid! Why would merchants refuse to buy my stuff? What the hell!?
I must sell everything. My back will have to endure.
Show me what you have. ::Barter.::
Why do you even carry all that junk with you?
What can you tell me about Core City?
What can you tell me about the Arena?
Why do you carry a human brain with you?
Have you ever been to Deep Caverns?
Why do you think the Faceless invaded Core City?
I gotta go. Goodbye.

It's not junk if I can sell it! Don't be such a zoner. I loot everything I can, then I go to a station, sell all of it and earn some coins, then go back to pick up things I couldn't carry with me. Then back to selling, yeah. But the stupid merchants won't buy my jun-- I mean loot. Loot!

Yeah, like, if the traders were a bit saner... then I'd say it isn't a bad place to sell loot. Yeah... But, as it currently stands it's... ugh! I mean, c'mon, really? I've got all this fine loot, and these derailed people won't buy all of it! "I can't buy all seventeen assault rifles. I'll take two." What kind of merchant are you? What is wrong with Underrail?

Never went to see a match in my life. I heard, listen to this, I heard that up until recently they didn't allow participants to loot the folks they zoned out. What? Seriously - what? Only now did they remember to do that, in these difficult times, when honest men depend on looting to survive?

Well, that's a cool lootin' tale: I was going through some backwater caves when I found this dead guy. Bald, ugly as siphoner's ass. A giant rock fell on his head and split it right open, yeah. You could see the brain, it was exposed and all. But, it was in good condition and, after I took his stuff, I decided to grab the brain too. I reckon, he won't need it anymore, and perhaps I'll find someone who'll buy it. It stinks a bit, but hell, life stinks in general.
No. I once pulled a button from one of the elevators that go down, but that's close to it as I've been. Why?
Thanks for reminding me! There is a lootin' potential there, yeah!
Oh come on! I just want to get rid of all this stuff!

It's painful, you know. ::He sighs.:: But, other than that... I don't know, I can't tell you much about the city. I mostly come here for the Hardcore City Bar and to see the merchants. ::He lowers his head and begins mumbling to himself.:: Stupid merchants...
C'mon! Just... c'mon! Who comes up with this stuff?
It's what I always say: Never miss a chance when it presents itself so conveniently!
I've found a warehouse block in Deep Caverns which is full of...
Just asking.
I'm just gonna wait for them to kill each other. ::He grins.:: Then the lootin' can begin!
You really think you'll earn much by selling animal organs and scrap metal?
Why don't you just drop all unnecessary things and just carry what's most valuable?
Well, I too have a problem with merchants not wanting to buy all my stuff.
Can we discuss something else?
Of what? C'mon, stop teasing me. Of what?
I heard there's good stuff there to be found, yeah. My grandad even went there to scavenge while the elevators were still working. He never came back.
It adds up, trust me. Bullet by bullet, heart by heart, battery by battery, yeah. It just adds up. It takes a while, but that's how *I* do things.

Are you derailed? Why would I drop perfectly good organs when someone *will* eventually buy them? Yeah, I pick up valuable stuff - I pick up everything! And I sell everything. At least I try to, but the stupid merchants have this, like, limit on what and how much they'll buy! Who came up with that?

I thought that absolutely everyone was derailed in this world, but you proved me wrong! I guess there is one person other than me that agrees with... me... Yeah!

Say, how would you like to buy some stuff?
Maybe we can discuss a trade!
Loot. As far as the eye can see.
What was his name?
Sorry to hear that.
::Al Fabet notices a screw on the ground and bends over - with some effort - to pick it up.:: Well, look at this treasure!
Ah, damn it, I dropped my screw! Can you see it anywhere?
I just want to maximize my loot selling potential. Although, my back is now going, "Well, kinda." Yeah, I wish weight didn't exist.
No.

::His eyes almost pop out of the mask the moment you deliver the magic word. Awe overwhelms him and his voice fills with excitement.::

How do I get there?
Percy.
Yeah. Life of a looter is a dangerous one.
Damn it! If I don't sell all this soon, my back's gonna break!
It's very dangerous, you should know. There's burrowers and other kinds of dangers there.
There is an elevator east of SGS which will take you down. Then you gotta follow the road north and you'll get to it eventually. Someone with your experience will easily find it.
Yeah, yeah. How do I get there?

I can't thank you enough for this. No one in my life was this good to me. Thank you. Thank you. When I get back I'm gonna get you... something. But it's gonna be something good, yeah. 

I gotta go.
Good luck, Al.
cc10
